What the graders are looking for: MUST list internal components, use all 5 methods on an item of your choice. Explain what you subtracted, divided, etc. and what the products looks like after that step. Include value, feasibility, and viability

 

Bulletin Board

Internal Components:

board frame, cork, pins, photos, stickers, command strips, magnets

 

Subtraction: 

-remove push pins, must glue/modge podge pictures down

-Value: Makes the board permanent, pictures will be harder to be lost or damaged

-Feasibility: not sure if glue works on cork?

-Viability: could give a cool collage sort of look different from the standard cork board, customers may be more likely to have glue accessible than push pins

Division: 

-make into multiple, smaller boards

-Value: more uses, more design power for the consumer, fits into smaller spaces, can be different shapes

-Feasibility: definitely, just make smaller cork and frame

-Viability: may interest some customers, but other may want the traditional rectangle board

Multiplication:

-increase the number of pictures; make it a virtual screen

-Value: more pictures can be added; easier to change out pictures; don't have to print pictures

-Feasibility: the technology exists

-Viability: would require a nearby outlet to plug it in and wifi to get the pictures

Task Unification: 

-Combine with a dry erase board calendar

-Value: Serves more than decorative purpose, used for organization, updated more than pictures

-Feasibility: cut out a part of the cork and glue in/attach calendar

-Viability: takes less wall space, serves multiple functions, good for small spaces

Attribute Dependency:

-if a picture has been there for a while, the pin will light up to highlight the memory of the picture and/or suggest that the picture is replaced with a more recent picture

-Value: Makes the board more dynamic, adds light, sparks a memory

-Feasibility: could definitely add a light to a push pin, a timer in the pin though might make it a little complicated

-Viability: depends on the interest, some may not want to spend more money for light-up push pins

Dishwasher

Internal Components:

Dishwashing compartment, dish racks, silverware basket, detergent dispenser, spray arms, door latch, mode/control pad

Subtraction

-Remove the mode/control pad so the dishwasher has only one mode.

-Value: Makes the dishwasher easier to use; no confusion on which mode to select.

-Feasibility: Highly feasible. Just a slight altercation would need to be made to remove the mode selection component.

-Viability: May interest some users as removal of the mode selection could decrease the product's cost.

Division

-Divide the washing aspect and drying aspect of the dishwasher into to different compartments

-Value: Could dry dishes better as there is less moisture in the compartment

-Feasibility: Definitely could be done. Would require two different machines and more space, like a washing machine and dryer.

-Viability: Unlikely that users would prefer this method. This would cost more money and take up more room, which is not ideal.

Multiplication

-Multiply the dishwasher space into separate compartments that can be ran separately

-Value: Don't have to completely fill dishwasher before running; can wash smaller loads of dishes, therefore using less water

-Feasibility: Possible. Capability already exists as there are multi-drawer dishwashers. Idea would be slightly altered to create more compartments

-Viability: May interest people who don't use many dishes. May not interest other users as price point may increase.

Task Unification

-Adding a reservoir for the dish-washing detergent that would dispense the proper amount of detergent needed for the load

-Value: User would not have to load detergent in every time they use the dishwasher, but rather every 50 uses (or so)

-Feasibility: Idea is possible. Think of it like a soda machine dispensing drink syrup when used. The technology exists.

-Viability: Users would like not having to load detergent every use. May take up just slightly more space, but would save time.

Attribute Dependency

-The dishwasher can detect how dirty the dishes inside are and adjust the length of the washing cycle accordingly

-Value: Would eliminate the need to rinse dishes before placing them in the dishwasher to be sure they come out clean.

-Feasibility: Not likely feasible. The technology to detect the dirtiness of the dishes would be complicated to create/program.

-Viability: If the technology could be created, users would most likely want it so they don't have to worry about setting the mode of the dishwasher correctly or rinsing dishes before putting them in the dishwasher.

-Feasibility: definitely, just make smaller cork and frame

-Viability: may interest some customers, but other may want the traditional rectangle board

Multiplication:

-increase the number of pictures; make it a virtual screen

-Value: more pictures can be added; easier to change out pictures; don't have to print pictures

-Feasibility: the technology exists

-Viability: would require a nearby outlet to plug it in and wifi to get the pictures

Task Unification: 

-Combine with a dry erase board calendar

-Value: Serves more than decorative purpose, used for organization, updated more than pictures

-Feasibility: cut out a part of the cork and glue in/attach calendar

-Viability: takes less wall space, serves multiple functions, good for small spaces

Attribute Dependency:

-if a picture has been there for a while, the pin will light up to highlight the memory of the picture and/or suggest that the picture is replaced with a more recent picture

-Value: Makes the board more dynamic, adds light, sparks a memory

-Feasibility: could definitely add a light to a push pin, a timer in the pin though might make it a little complicated

-Viability: depends on the interest, some may not want to spend more money for light-up push pins

Dishwasher

Internal Components:

Dishwashing compartment, dish racks, silverware basket, detergent dispenser, spray arms, door latch, mode/control pad

Subtraction

-Remove the mode/control pad so the dishwasher has only one mode.

-Value: Makes the dishwasher easier to use; no confusion on which mode to select.

-Feasibility: Highly feasible. Just a slight altercation would need to be made to remove the mode selection component.

-Viability: May interest some users as removal of the mode selection could decrease the product's cost.

Division

-Divide the washing aspect and drying aspect of the dishwasher into to different compartments

-Value: Could dry dishes better as there is less moisture in the compartment

-Feasibility: Definitely could be done. Would require two different machines and more space, like a washing machine and dryer.

-Viability: Unlikely that users would prefer this method. This would cost more money and take up more room, which is not ideal.

Multiplication

-Multiply the dishwasher space into separate compartments that can be ran separately

-Value: Don't have to completely fill dishwasher before running; can wash smaller loads of dishes, therefore using less water

-Feasibility: Possible. Capability already exists as there are multi-drawer dishwashers. Idea would be slightly altered to create more compartments

-Viability: May interest people who don't use many dishes. May not interest other users as price point may increase.

Task Unification

-Adding a reservoir for the dish-washing detergent that would dispense the proper amount of detergent needed for the load

-Value: User would not have to load detergent in every time they use the dishwasher, but rather every 50 uses (or so)

-Feasibility: Idea is possible. Think of it like a soda machine dispensing drink syrup when used. The technology exists.

-Viability: Users would like not having to load detergent every use. May take up just slightly more space, but would save time.

Attribute Dependency

-The dishwasher can detect how dirty the dishes inside are and adjust the length of the washing cycle accordingly

-Value: Would eliminate the need to rinse dishes before placing them in the dishwasher to be sure they come out clean.

-Feasibility: Not likely feasible. The technology to detect the dirtiness of the dishes would be complicated to create/program.

-Viability: If the technology could be created, users would most likely want it so they don't have to worry about setting the mode of the dishwasher correctly or rinsing dishes before putting them in the dishwasher.
